check out that anime

00:10:25.250 --> 00:10:26.459 position:50% align:center
you two were just talking about.

00:10:26.543 --> 00:10:27.585 position:50% align:center
[SETSUNA]
Huh?

00:10:27.669 --> 00:10:29.754 position:50% align:center
This Jackal character
sure sounds fun.

00:10:29.838 --> 00:10:32.257 position:50% align:center
And hearing your
excitement got me excited!

00:10:32.340 --> 00:10:36.302 position:50% align:center
[gasps] The whole series is fun!

00:10:36.386 --> 00:10:38.263 position:50% align:center
Then let's use the
rest of our session

00:10:38.346 --> 00:10:40.473 position:50% align:center
to sing anime theme songs!

00:10:40.557 --> 00:10:42.308 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Yeah!

00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:47.897 position:50% align:center
Delicious!

00:10:47.981 --> 00:10:50.442 position:50% align:center
They're my grandma's
special nuka blend pickles.

00:10:50.525 --> 00:10:53.319 position:50% align:center
They really do taste like they
were homemade with love.

00:10:53.403 --> 00:10:54.612 position:50% align:center
[AI]
It's true!

00:10:54.696 --> 00:10:57.866 position:50% align:center
[KASUMI] Egh. What is that
weird smell in here?

00:10:57.949 --> 00:10:59.367 position:50% align:center
The scent of yummy food!

00:10:59.451 --> 00:11:00.827 position:50% align:center
Welcome back, everyone.

00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:01.870 position:50% align:center
[EMMA]
Can I try some?

00:11:01.953 --> 00:11:03.329 position:50% align:center
[YU]
I take it you're all done?

00:11:03.413 --> 00:11:06.666 position:50% align:center
[KANATA]
I'm so exhausted from today.

00:11:06.750 --> 00:11:08.418 position:50% align:center
[EMMA]
Yeah, but we got a lot done!

00:11:08.501 --> 00:11:10.086 position:50% align:center
Oh! That's right.

00:11:10.170 --> 00:11:11.713 position:50% align:center
Kasumi, if you
don't mind staying,

00:11:11.796 --> 00:11:13.214 position:50% align:center
I'd like a word with you.

00:11:13.298 --> 00:11:15.675 position:50% align:center
Hey, I apologized
like a bajillion times

00:11:15.759 --> 00:11:17.218 position:50% align:center
for the glasses, didn't I?

00:11:17.302 --> 00:11:19.846 position:50% align:center
That's not what I wanna discuss.

00:11:21.139 --> 00:11:24.184 position:50% align:center
[KANATA] So, the plan is to
meet up on Saturday, as well?

00:11:24.267 --> 00:11:26.770 position:50% align:center
[EMMA] Yup. We're going
jogging in Odaiba.

00:11:26.853 --> 00:11:28.396 position:50% align:center
It's gonna be rough.

00:11:28.480 --> 00:11:30.523 position:50% align:center
I'll jog along with you,
if you don't mind.

00:11:30.607 --> 00:11:33.109 position:50% align:center
Running is great,
so the more, the merrier!

00:11:33.193 --> 00:11:35.945 position:50% align:center
Shouldn't you be running off
to Drama Club pretty soon?

00:11:36.029 --> 00:11:36.821 position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:11:36.905 --> 00:11:39.532 position:50% align:center
Two clubs at once. Must be hard.

00:11:39.616 --> 00:11:42.285 position:50% align:center
I really love both,
so I don't mind.

00:11:42.369 --> 00:11:45.497 position:50% align:center
And you participate in some of
the sports clubs, don't you, Ai?

00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:49.459 position:50% align:center
Sure do! So, I apologize in
advance if I'm late tomorrow.

00:11:49.542 --> 00:11:53.588 position:50% align:center
You two are an inspiration
to us all. [yawns]

00:11:53.672 --> 00:11:56.716 position:50% align:center
Whatcha think of our club?

00:11:56.800 --> 00:11:58.551 position:50% align:center
It's fun.

00:11:58.635 --> 00:12:00.053 position:50% align:center
[EMMA]
Hm?

00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:02.847 position:50% align:center
This has gotta be the most
excited I've ever seen Rinari!

00:12:02.931 --> 00:12:05.141 position:50% align:center
Though, I can't say I blame her!

00:12:05.225 --> 00:12:07.435 position:50% align:center
It might be hard to tell
since I'm not very good

00:12:07.519 --> 00:12:10.271 position:50% align:center
at expressing how I feel.

00:12:10.355 --> 00:12:12.857 position:50% align:center
I'm just glad that you're
both enjoying yourselves.

00:12:12.941 --> 00:12:15.360 position:50% align:center
How can we not when your
club's doing so many things

00:12:15.443 --> 00:12:17.445 position:50% align:center
that I've never seen
other clubs even try?

00:12:17.529 --> 00:12:19.406 position:50% align:center
The Idol Club's that unique?

00:12:19.489 --> 00:12:22.909 position:50% align:center
Definitely! Kasumin said we
all had the correct answer

00:12:22.992 --> 00:12:24.452 position:50% align:center
when it comes to
what idols need.

00:12:24.536 --> 00:12:26.454 position:50% align:center
And she's 100% right about that!

00:12:26.538 --> 00:12:29.124 position:50% align:center
We all have different answers
'cause we're different people.

00:12:29.207 --> 00:12:30.375 position:50% align:center
But at the same time,

00:12:30.458 --> 00:12:31.960 position:50% align:center
you're all so sweet and
fun that you still have

00:12:32.043 --> 00:12:34.254 position:50% align:center
something in common
at the end of the day!

00:12:34.337 --> 00:12:36.381 position:50% align:center
And the thought of everyone's
individual talents

00:12:36.464 --> 00:12:38.967 position:50% align:center
coming together to form a
totally mind-blowing concert

00:12:39.050 --> 00:12:41.678 position:50% align:center
gets me so stoked!

00:12:41.761 --> 00:12:44.139 position:50% align:center
Ai's one of the brighter
crayons in the box.

00:12:44.222 --> 00:12:45.015 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Uh?

00:12:45.098 --> 00:12:46.975 position:50% align:center
All of us are pretty different.

00:12:47.058 --> 00:12:48.268 position:50% align:center
Which means there's something

00:12:48.351 --> 00:12:51.187 position:50% align:center
we've been avoiding
that we need to consider.

00:12:52.689 --> 00:12:54.607 position:50% align:center
[KASUMI]
Solo idols?

00:12:54.691 --> 00:12:56.359 position:50% align:center
Although it's a step
in a new direction,

00:12:56.443 --> 00:12:59.904 position:50% align:center
it's not a bad idea.
We'd still share a stage,

00:12:59.988 --> 00:13:02.657 position:50% align:center
but we'd be standing
on it as solo idols.

00:13:02.741 --> 00:13:04.409 position:50% align:center
I'm sure it's crossed
everyone's minds,

00:13:04.492 --> 00:13:07.203 position:50% align:center
even though we haven't
discussed it before.

00:13:07.287 --> 00:13:10.206 position:50% align:center
Yeah, but...
saying it is one thing.

00:13:10.290 --> 00:13:13.168 position:50% align:center
Actually going through
with it is another.

00:13:14.836 --> 00:13:17.672 position:50% align:center
[RINA]
Standing on stage by myself?

00:13:17.756 --> 00:13:20.550 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't do it on a
whim, that's for sure.

00:13:20.633 --> 00:13:23.511 position:50% align:center
We could rely on each other
if we perform as a group.

00:13:23.595 --> 00:13:25.513 position:50% align:center
But getting on stage
as a solo idol

00:13:25.597 --> 00:13:28.933 position:50% align:center
means losing the backup
you get from a team.

00:13:29.017 --> 00:13:31.728 position:50% align:center
Honestly? I'm worried.

00:13:31.811 --> 00:13:34.731 position:50% align:center
What if I can't do something
on my own, or even if I can,

00:13:34.814 --> 00:13:37.776 position:50% align:center
what if the people I
perform for don't like it?

00:13:42.280 --> 00:13:46.993 position:50% align:center
[AI] It'd be so much easier if
there was only one right answer.

00:13:47.077 --> 00:13:50.455 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:13:50.538 --> 00:13:52.707 position:50% align:center
--Yeah!
--Ai!

00:13:52.791 --> 00:13:56.586 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Every sport has a set of rules.

00:13:56.670 --> 00:13:59.506 position:50% align:center
But rules don't apply to school
idols because the only thing

00:13:59.589 --> 00:14:01.800 position:50% align:center
that limits us is
our imagination.

00:14:01.883 --> 00:14:03.885 position:50% align:center
We're on our own.

00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:08.390 position:50% align:center
[AI] I haven't had much
time to think about this,

00:14:08.473 --> 00:14:11.017 position:50% align:center
but what kind of school
idol do I wanna be?

00:14:11.101 --> 00:14:15.730 position:50% align:center
Or rather, what kind of
person do I wanna be?

00:14:15.814 --> 00:14:20.944 position:50% align:center
I wonder... which path
is the right one for me?

00:14:21.027 --> 00:14:21.945 position:50% align:center
[phone chimes]

00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:23.238 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Hm?

00:14:24.489 --> 00:14:25.657 position:50% align:center
[KASUMI]
Don't forget!

00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:27.283 position:50% align:center
We're meeting at Rainbow
Park tomorrow morning

00:14:27.367 --> 00:14:29.536 position:50% align:center
at nine o'clock sharp
for our jog!

00:14:29.619 --> 00:14:31.996 position:50% align:center
[RINA]
Roger!

00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:33.873 position:50% align:center
[KANATA]
Okay.

00:15:23.715 --> 00:15:26.343 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I still have an hour to kill.

00:15:45.278 --> 00:15:46.279 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Yo, Emma!

00:15:46.363 --> 00:15:48.031 position:50% align:center
Oh! Hey, Ai!

00:15:48.114 --> 00:15:49.657 position:50% align:center
What's going on?

00:15:49.741 --> 00:15:51.993 position:50% align:center
[EMMA] I just got here early
'cause I woke up early.

00:15:52.077 --> 00:15:53.495 position:50% align:center
What about you?

00:15:53.578 --> 00:15:55.497 position:50% align:center
Same thing.

00:15:56.414 --> 00:15:57.791 position:50% align:center
[EMMA] Were you surprised
when we mentioned

00:15:57.874 --> 00:15:59.793 position:50% align:center
solo idols yesterday?

00:15:59.876 --> 00:16:03.797 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Huh? Truth be told, yeah, I was.

00:16:03.880 --> 00:16:06.883 position:50% align:center
But what I wound up being most
surprised about was myself.

00:16:06.966 --> 00:16:08.259 position:50% align:center
[EMMA]
Hm?

00:16:08.343 --> 00:16:09.928 position:50% align:center
[AI] The thing everyone seems
to be concerned with

00:16:10.011 --> 00:16:14.140 position:50% align:center
is if they'll be able to fully
express themselves on stage.

00:16:14.224 --> 00:16:17.644 position:50% align:center
I've helped out so many
clubs at Nijigasaki.

00:16:17.727 --> 00:16:19.145 position:50% align:center
But you know what?

00:16:19.229 --> 00:16:22.065 position:50% align:center
They had that "teamwork makes
the dream work" mentality.

00:16:22.148 --> 00:16:26.319 position:50% align:center
So, I'm not used to
doing things alone.

00:16:30.198 --> 00:16:33.034 position:50% align:center
[AI] It's different from
what I'm used to.

00:16:37.163 --> 00:16:38.456 position:50% align:center
[EMMA] Why don't we
head out so the others

00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:41.418 position:50% align:center
don't think we ran away?

00:16:41.501 --> 00:16:44.671 position:50% align:center
They said nine. Don't wanna
race against the clock!

00:16:46.673 --> 00:16:49.259 position:50% align:center
Are you all right?

00:16:49.342 --> 00:16:52.512 position:50% align:center
[laughing] That's hilarious!

00:16:52.595 --> 00:16:53.847 position:50% align:center
Wait, wha--?

00:16:53.930 --> 00:16:55.390 position:50% align:center
[AI] First you said the
thing about running away,

00:16:55.473 --> 00:16:57.642 position:50% align:center
and topped that with
"race against the clock"?

00:16:57.726 --> 00:16:59.894 position:50% align:center
You're too good at puns Emma!

00:16:59.978 --> 00:17:02.355 position:50% align:center
I am? Oh!

00:17:02.439 --> 00:17:04.107 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Those were awesome!

00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:07.610 position:50% align:center
I didn't even realize
I was being funny.

00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:11.239 position:50% align:center
[AI, EMMA laughing]

00:17:11.322 --> 00:17:13.533 position:50% align:center
[AI sighs]

00:17:13.616 --> 00:17:16.619 position:50% align:center
[EMMA] I'm so happy you chose
to join the School Idol Club.

00:17:16.703 --> 00:17:18.496 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Oh? Why's that?

00:17:18.580 --> 00:17:21.082 position:50% align:center
Because you're a
perpetual ray of sunshine.

00:17:21.166 --> 00:17:23.251 position:50% align:center
[AI] I guess it's hard for me
to see since I don't know

00:17:23.335 --> 00:17:24.377 position:50% align:center
what I want right now.

00:17:24.461 --> 00:17:25.795 position:50% align:center
You don't have to know,

00:17:25.879 --> 00:17:28.423 position:50% align:center
you can still be your fun self
while you figure it out.

00:17:28.506 --> 00:17:29.507 position:50% align:center
[AI gasps]

00:17:29.591 --> 00:17:32.844 position:50% align:center
Recently, our club disbanded,

00:17:32.927 --> 00:17:36.973 position:50% align:center
but we managed to come back
together and try it again.

00:17:37.057 --> 00:17:39.642 position:50% align:center
All of us have things
that we worry about.

00:17:39.726 --> 00:17:41.686 position:50% align:center
And yet I can't help
but think we're also

00:17:41.770 --> 00:17:43.688 position:50% align:center
looking at the future
with bright eyes,

00:17:43.772 --> 00:17:46.107 position:50% align:center
anticipating what
it has in store.

00:17:46.191 --> 00:17:49.569 position:50% align:center
Oddly enough, that's what
makes us worry, too.

00:17:49.652 --> 00:17:51.571 position:50% align:center
We know there's a step
we need to take,

00:17:51.654 --> 00:17:54.407 position:50% align:center
we just need the
courage to take it.

00:17:54.491 --> 00:17:57.744 position:50% align:center
Your positivity's contagious and
I've seen so many more smiles

00:17:57.827 --> 00:17:59.996 position:50% align:center
on the girls' faces
since you joined!

00:18:00.080 --> 00:18:02.665 position:50% align:center
You think so? But I
haven't done that much.

00:18:02.749 --> 00:18:05.210 position:50% align:center
And that makes it all
the more amazing.

00:18:05.293 --> 00:18:06.378 position:50% align:center
By being myself?

00:18:06.461 --> 00:18:08.463 position:50% align:center
[EMMA]
By being yourself.

00:18:08.546 --> 00:18:10.590 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:18:12.008 --> 00:18:14.177 position:50% align:center
So that's it.

00:18:23.937 --> 00:18:26.773 position:50% align:center
You're the best!
Thank you! I am so pumped!

00:18:26.856 --> 00:18:28.817 position:50% align:center
Where're you going?

00:18:29.859 --> 00:18:31.736 position:50% align:center
[AI]
The answer was simple.

00:18:31.820 --> 00:18:34.531 position:50% align:center
I love it when the people
around me are having fun.

00:18:34.614 --> 00:18:38.118 position:50% align:center
And it's even better when
I'm having fun with them!

00:18:38.201 --> 00:18:40.120 position:50% align:center
What would be even better
is if we could share

00:18:40.203 --> 00:18:43.164 position:50% align:center
those positive feelings
as school idols!

00:18:43.248 --> 00:18:46.876 position:50% align:center
If we can do that, I can run
down this uncharted path!

00:18:46.960 --> 00:18:49.004 position:50% align:center
Wherever it may lead!

00:18:50.130 --> 00:18:52.048 position:50% align:center
[AI]
I say bring it on!

00:18:52.132 --> 00:18:54.300 position:50% align:center
[AI laughs]

00:20:41.616 --> 00:20:45.870 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:20:48.456 --> 00:20:50.542 position:50% align:center
[AI]
All of these people were here.

00:20:50.625 --> 00:20:54.170 position:50% align:center
We're never completely
alone on a stage!

00:20:54.254 --> 00:20:56.631 position:50% align:center
So awesome!

00:20:56.715 --> 00:21:01.094 position:50% align:center
I didn't expect that, but she
completely owned that stage!

00:21:01.177 --> 00:21:04.431 position:50% align:center
I wanna see all of you sing
and dance just like she did!

00:21:04.514 --> 00:21:06.349 position:50% align:center
Everybody's so
uniquely themselves,

00:21:06.433 --> 00:21:07.475 position:50% align:center
and I truly believe that

00:21:07.559 --> 00:21:09.561 position:50% align:center
the possibilities for
you are endless!

00:21:09.644 --> 00:21:11.938 position:50% align:center
I just can't wait to see
the shows you put on!

00:21:12.022 --> 00:21:14.065 position:50% align:center
Because I know whatever
you girls decide to do,

00:21:14.149 --> 00:21:16.651 position:50% align:center
it's gonna be great!

00:21:16.735 --> 00:21:19.612 position:50% align:center
You know, Yu. Takes a
great girl to know one.

00:21:19.696 --> 00:21:21.281 position:50% align:center
[YU]
Huh?

00:21:21.364 --> 00:21:23.658 position:50% align:center
Kanata's right about that!

00:21:23.742 --> 00:21:25.243 position:50% align:center
I'm feeling pumped.

00:21:25.326 --> 00:21:26.202 position:50% align:center
[EMMA]
Mm!

00:21:26.286 --> 00:21:27.704 position:50% align:center
[SETSUNA laughs]

00:21:28.413 --> 00:21:30.123 position:50% align:center
Me, too!

00:23:04.968 --> 00:23:06.678 position:50% align:center
[AI]
You may be a second-year, Ayumu,

00:23:06.761 --> 00:23:10.098 position:50% align:center
but your cuteness is only
second to your voice!

00:23:10.181 --> 00:23:13.476 position:50% align:center
That jog made my emotions run
high cause you know, jogging!

00:23:13.560 --> 00:23:15.228 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:23:15.311 --> 00:23:16.855 position:50% align:center
[AI]
We may be the School Idol Club,

00:23:16.938 --> 00:23:20.775 position:50% align:center
but we can't just
wait idol-y by.

00:23:20.859 --> 00:23:22.944 position:50% align:center
[YU] Please, stop.
I can't take anymore.

00:23:23.028 --> 00:23:25.447 position:50% align:center
She's really into
Ai's jokes, huh?

00:23:25.530 --> 00:23:27.741 position:50% align:center
Yu's always had a
childish sense of humor

00:23:27.824 --> 00:23:31.286 position:50% align:center
since we were kids, and she
just never grew out of it.

00:23:31.369 --> 00:23:33.621 position:50% align:center
Where did all these
puns come from?

00:23:33.705 --> 00:23:36.833 position:50% align:center
They're a crucial part to
my school idol training!

00:23:36.916 --> 00:23:38.251 position:50% align:center
[EMMA laughs]

00:23:47.052 --> 00:23:50.930 position:50% align:center
[EMMA] Next time, "Something
I Can Only Do Right Now."